I've told you that...

286
00:43:50.462 --> 00:43:52.213
I don't want to discuss that.

287
00:43:54.215 --> 00:43:55.050
Yoo-jin.

288
00:43:55.675 --> 00:43:58.136
Somebody has to bring it up.

289
00:43:58.970 --> 00:44:01.681
Wouldn't it hurt less if I did it?

290
00:44:03.933 --> 00:44:04.768
Right?

291
00:44:06.936 --> 00:44:10.357
Everyone has a problem
they don't want to discuss.

292
00:44:16.821 --> 00:44:18.406
For instance. for you.

293
00:44:19.449 --> 00:44:21.159
your son.

294
00:44:22.952 --> 00:44:24.537
Commercials are over.

295
00:44:24.621 --> 00:44:26.414
Returning now. Mics on. please.

296
00:44:28.333 --> 00:44:30.752
Let's get started.

297
00:44:34.005 --> 00:44:36.424
Sorry. I got carried away.

298
00:44:38.009 --> 00:44:38.968
Yes. Ji-hyeon.

299
00:44:39.969 --> 00:44:41.429
Stick to the script.

300
00:44:58.196 --> 00:45:01.950
The interview today was so heartwarming.

301
00:45:02.033 --> 00:45:04.035
Really? Thanks.

302
00:45:04.119 --> 00:45:04.994
I was so nervous.

303
00:45:05.078 --> 00:45:07.705
No. you sounded so natural.

304
00:45:07.789 --> 00:45:09.749
and looked so beautiful.

305
00:45:12.085 --> 00:45:13.128
Excuse us.

306
00:45:13.420 --> 00:45:14.421
-What?
-Yes.

307
00:45:14.963 --> 00:45:17.048
All good. I'll take care of it.

308
00:45:17.132 --> 00:45:18.341
Oh. yeah. ma'am.

309
00:45:18.716 --> 00:45:19.551
Oh. wait.

310
00:45:25.390 --> 00:45:26.933
Thanks for today.

311
00:45:27.016 --> 00:45:29.978
I baked these myself. Hope they're good.

312
00:45:30.353 --> 00:45:32.689
I'm so touched. ma'am.

313
00:45:33.064 --> 00:45:35.066
Can I take a picture of it?

314
00:45:35.525 --> 00:45:36.359
What?

315
00:45:36.901 --> 00:45:39.571
No need.

316
00:45:48.621 --> 00:45:51.708
I can't even eat it. I'll keep it forever.

317
00:45:53.209 --> 00:45:54.085
Thank you.

318
00:46:09.601 --> 00:46:10.435
Again?

319
00:46:11.227 --> 00:46:12.353
Which one?

320
00:46:12.645 --> 00:46:14.772
We're not finished investigating yet.

321
00:46:15.982 --> 00:46:17.150
but Senator Park...

322
00:46:17.525 --> 00:46:20.153
Tale as old as time.

323
00:46:34.459 --> 00:46:36.628
<i>Cookies baked by the Madam herself.</i>

324
00:46:36.711 --> 00:46:39.631
<i>Behind it is her twenty-year-old bag.</i>

325
00:46:39.714 --> 00:46:43.510
<i>I love and respect you. Madam.
Heart. heart.</i>

326
00:46:43.593 --> 00:46:46.387
-What are you doing?
-Literally in love.

327
00:46:46.471 --> 00:46:48.306
She baked these herself.

328
00:46:49.057 --> 00:46:50.308
Really?

329
00:46:50.391 --> 00:46:51.935
-Let's share them!
-No!

330
00:46:52.018 --> 00:46:53.520
It's my family heirloom now.

331
00:46:53.603 --> 00:46:56.189
-Come on.
-Admire the picture instead.

332
00:46:56.272 --> 00:46:57.565
Wow.

333
00:46:58.399 --> 00:46:59.317
Lovely!

334
00:47:10.036 --> 00:47:10.954
What should we do?

335
00:47:13.831 --> 00:47:15.833
Just say someone broke in

336
00:47:17.168 --> 00:47:19.504
and took our campaign promises document.

337
00:47:19.879 --> 00:47:21.047
Yes. ma'am.

338
00:47:22.924 --> 00:47:26.010
So. the girl...

339
00:47:26.386 --> 00:47:28.805
Keep for now.

340
00:47:30.431 --> 00:47:33.309
-She'll be useful later.
-Yes. ma'am.

341
00:47:37.397 --> 00:47:38.523
I'm good.

342
00:47:49.826 --> 00:47:52.370
I got more wrinkles.

343
00:47:54.998 --> 00:47:56.082
How old is she?

344
00:47:57.208 --> 00:47:58.042
What?

345
00:47:58.960 --> 00:48:01.588
The...girl.

346
00:48:03.506 --> 00:48:05.800
Around late twenties.

347
00:48:09.429 --> 00:48:11.598
Not underage this time. then.

348
00:48:20.815 --> 00:48:21.649
It's me.

349
00:48:22.442 --> 00:48:25.278
I'm eating your homecooked
breakfast from tomorrow?

350
00:48:29.657 --> 00:48:31.618
You looked good on television.

351
00:48:33.202 --> 00:48:34.621
Oh. okay.

352
00:48:34.704 --> 00:48:36.789
I'm guessing you took care of it.

353
00:48:37.874 --> 00:48:42.420
And regarding the banner handyman.

354
00:48:43.212 --> 00:48:44.922
please take special care of him.

355
00:48:47.050 --> 00:48:48.801
He happened to see

356
00:48:49.719 --> 00:48:51.387
my face. you know?

357
00:48:52.180 --> 00:48:55.266
Banner...handyman?

358
00:49:00.980 --> 00:49:02.023
I see.

359
00:49:12.700 --> 00:49:13.993
Hello? Preisdent Guk?

360
00:49:14.786 --> 00:49:15.620
Yes.

361
00:49:19.415 --> 00:49:21.334
What are you hiding from me?

362
00:49:21.417 --> 00:49:24.337
What could I hide from you?

363
00:49:24.420 --> 00:49:25.421
How dare I...

364
00:49:25.505 --> 00:49:27.590
I shouldn't be feeling this way.

365
00:49:28.591 --> 00:49:30.301
but I'm disappointed in you.

366
00:49:30.968 --> 00:49:32.804
Ma'am. no. please.

367
00:49:32.887 --> 00:49:35.264
I just didn't want to bother you

368
00:49:35.348 --> 00:49:36.891
with small matters...

369
00:49:36.974 --> 00:49:39.560
Yes. yes. I'm so sorry.

370
00:49:39.644 --> 00:49:42.105
I'll take care of it and get back to you.

371
00:49:42.689 --> 00:49:44.524
Yes. have a great evening.

372
00:49:47.151 --> 00:49:50.238
How does she know already?

373
00:49:51.447 --> 00:49:53.032
Strike team is out?

374
00:49:53.324 --> 00:49:55.451
Yes. they'll get him soon.

375
00:49:56.452 --> 00:49:59.997
All for a handyman.

376
00:50:25.481 --> 00:50:27.400
-Is this the only angle?
-Yes.

377
00:50:29.819 --> 00:50:31.320
Wait a minute. Go back.

378
00:50:32.864 --> 00:50:33.740
Yes. there.

379
00:50:38.828 --> 00:50:39.704
What...

380
00:51:08.566 --> 00:51:10.693
Secretary Jo.

381
00:51:10.777 --> 00:51:12.987
-Return the strike team.
-What?

382
00:51:13.070 --> 00:51:15.448
Or we'll all die.

383
00:51:17.658 --> 00:51:19.160
What do you mean?

384
00:51:45.561 --> 00:51:46.729
Secretary Jo.

385
00:51:47.396 --> 00:51:49.649
You've become a good bluffer ever since

386
00:51:49.732 --> 00:51:50.983
working for a senator.

387
00:51:51.067 --> 00:51:52.151
They'll be in danger.

388
00:51:52.235 --> 00:51:53.986
Come on.

389
00:51:54.070 --> 00:51:56.656
Captain Jo. I mean...

390
00:51:56.739 --> 00:52:00.910
Secretary Jo. you used to have him in
your special mission unit. you said?

391
00:52:01.160 --> 00:52:02.078
Yes.

392
00:52:22.557 --> 00:52:23.850
I got it.

393
00:52:24.225 --> 00:52:27.353
You want to make a point about

394
00:52:27.770 --> 00:52:30.231
how strong your mission unit was.

395
00:52:30.314 --> 00:52:31.899
-No.
-Secretary Jo!

396
00:52:32.775 --> 00:52:35.611
You seem to have trouble understanding.

397
00:52:35.695 --> 00:52:38.531
I also value my life.

398
00:52:38.614 --> 00:52:42.618
so I sent a whole strike team
to capture a handyman.

399
00:52:43.286 --> 00:52:46.038
The JSS Squad.

400
00:52:46.122 --> 00:52:47.915
the best in Korea.

401
00:52:49.917 --> 00:52:52.587
You'll see what I mean soon.

402
00:52:55.464 --> 00:52:56.549
Oh. well. well!

403
00:52:57.008 --> 00:52:59.010
That douchebag.

404
00:53:35.630 --> 00:53:36.505
Hurry.

405
00:56:28.177 --> 00:56:29.178
Status report!

406
00:56:30.137 --> 00:56:31.055
Status report!

407
00:56:31.680 --> 00:56:32.515
Status report!

408
00:56:34.391 --> 00:56:35.434
Status report!

409
00:58:11.697 --> 00:58:13.449
What's going on?

410
00:58:19.079 --> 00:58:20.372
What happened?

411
00:58:28.047 --> 00:58:30.424
-I'm glad.
-What?

412
00:58:31.550 --> 00:58:32.509
What do you mean?

413
00:58:34.011 --> 00:58:35.095
No one's dead.

414
00:58:52.363 --> 00:58:54.198
You're still in the living room?

415
00:58:55.824 --> 00:58:58.160
I'll be sleeping late tonight.
I'm waiting...

416
00:58:58.244 --> 00:58:59.203
on a report.

417
00:59:01.080 --> 00:59:01.914
Why?

418
00:59:02.748 --> 00:59:05.626
There's another troublemaker besides me?

419
00:59:21.308 --> 00:59:22.768
Your daughter.

420
00:59:41.954 --> 00:59:42.913
Anna?

421
00:59:45.958 --> 00:59:47.459
She ran away again.

422
00:59:49.795 --> 00:59:53.090
She should've learned by now. really.

423
01:00:05.769 --> 01:00:07.313
Must be the bad genes.

424
01:00:21.118 --> 01:00:22.536
If something happens to her.

425
01:00:26.749 --> 01:00:29.752
our deal is off.

426
01:01:57.381 --> 01:01:58.549
Bravo!

427
01:02:36.670 --> 01:02:37.671
What's wrong?

428
01:02:40.090 --> 01:02:41.216
What's she doing?

429
01:03:15.417 --> 01:03:16.710
SLEEP AID

430
01:03:58.418 --> 01:04:00.671
You mean you missed that headline?

431
01:04:01.338 --> 01:04:04.007
We couldn't have captured him with JSS.

432
01:04:04.508 --> 01:04:05.425
Who sent you?

433
01:04:05.634 --> 01:04:08.762
By the second time
I come to you. you will die.

434
01:04:08.845 --> 01:04:12.099
I saw something at where
I wasn't supposed to be.

435
01:04:12.349 --> 01:04:13.267
I'm sorry.

436
01:04:14.393 --> 01:04:16.353
Pretty. just like your mother.

437
01:04:16.812 --> 01:04:18.272
I remember everything.

438
01:04:18.605 --> 01:04:20.148
Mom didn't kill herself.

439
01:04:21.149 --> 01:04:22.359
That child is the reason.

440
01:04:22.442 --> 01:04:25.696
That's why I had to live as her puppet

440
01:04:26.305 --> 01:05:26.236
